{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CzdbrXVXXRUfdHxAJycFPp","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Here is the complete file contents of `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/lib/auth-api.ts`:\n\n## File: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/lib/auth-api.ts`\n\n**Key API Wrapper Pattern:**\n\n1. **Backend URL Configuration** (lines 5-8):\n   - Reads from environment variable `VITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL` with fallback to `http://127.0.0.1:3100`\n   - Strips trailing slash for consistent endpoint construction\n\n2. **Response Type Interfaces** (lines 10-28):\n   - `ChallengeResponse`: nonce, message, expiresAt\n   - `VerifyResponse`: accessToken, accessExpiresAt, refreshToken, refreshExpiresAt\n   - `RefreshResponse`: same as VerifyResponse\n\n3. **parseResponse Utility** (lines 30-37):\n   - Generic utility function that parses JSON and handles errors\n   - Checks `res.ok` status\n   - If error: extracts error message from `json.error` or falls back to status code message\n   - If success: returns typed JSON response\n   - **Error handling**: throws `Error` with descriptive message\n\n4. **API Function Pattern** (lines 39-76):\n   - All functions follow a consistent structure:\n     - Construct URL from `BACKEND_URL` constant\n     - POST requests with `Content-Type: application/json`\n     - Serialize payload with `JSON.stringify()`\n     - Call `parseResponse<T>(res)` for type-safe parsing\n   - Functions: `requestChallenge()`, `verifyChallenge()`, `refreshSession()`, `logout()`\n   - No Authorization header pattern shown (challenge-response auth, so tokens passed as request body, not header)\n\n5. **Notable Pattern**:\n   - The `logout()` function (line 70) does not return a typed response — it just makes the fetch call\n   - All other functions return typed promises\n\nThis is a clean, minimal wrapper pattern with a shared `parseResponse` utility for consistent error handling a