equests with `Content-Type: application/json`\n     - Serialize payload with `JSON.stringify()`\n     - Call `parseResponse<T>(res)` for type-safe parsing\n   - Functions: `requestChallenge()`, `verifyChallenge()`, `refreshSession()`, `logout()`\n   - No Authorization header pattern shown (challenge-response auth, so tokens passed as request body, not header)\n\n5. **Notable Pattern**:\n   - The `logout()` function (line 70) does not return a typed response — it just makes the fetch call\n   - All other functions return typed promises\n\nThis is a clean, minimal wrapper pattern with a shared `parseResponse` utility for consistent error handling and type safety."}],"totalDurationMs":9950,"totalTokens":37083,"totalToolUseCount":1,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6513,"cache_read_input_tokens":30049,"output_tokens":516,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":6513},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
